vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
title: |md
  ## kmalloc GFP Flag Decision Tree
  **GFP_KERNEL vs GFP_ATOMIC: Choose Based on Execution Context**
| {near: top-center}
# ─── ROOT DECISION ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
root: "Are you in process context?\n(syscall handler, workqueue,\nkernel thread)" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#E8EAF6"
    stroke: "#3949AB"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-size: 15
    bold: true
  }
}
# ─── INTERRUPT CONTEXT BRANCH (NO from root) ─────────────────────────────────
irq_ctx: "Interrupt / Softirq /\nTasklet Context" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFCDD2"
    stroke: "#C62828"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 14
    bold: true
  }
}
gfp_atomic_only: "GFP_ATOMIC  ONLY" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#EF9A9A"
    stroke: "#B71C1C"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-size: 16
    bold: true
  }
}
irq_note: |md
  **Why:** Scheduler cannot be invoked.
  Sleeping is physically impossible.
  `GFP_KERNEL` here → immediate BUG()
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFEBEE"
    stroke: "#C62828"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-size: 12
    italic: true
  }
}
# ─── PROCESS CONTEXT BRANCH (YES from root) ──────────────────────────────────
proc_ctx: "Process Context\nConfirmed" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#E8F5E9"
    stroke: "#2E7D32"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 14
    bold: true
  }
}
can_sleep: "Are you holding a spinlock\nor in an atomic section?" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#FFF8E1"
    stroke: "#F57F17"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-size: 14
    bold: true
  }
}
# ─── CAN SLEEP → GFP_KERNEL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
gfp_kernel: "GFP_KERNEL" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#A5D6A7"
    stroke: "#1B5E20"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-size: 18
    bold: true
  }
}
kernel_props: |md
  **Behavior:**
  - May call `schedule()` — puts caller to sleep
  - Triggers page reclaim (kswapd)
  - May wait for writeback / compaction
  - Draws from full memory pool
  **Success rate:** Highest
  **Latency:** Variable (µs – ms under pressure)
  **Valid contexts:** Syscall handlers, `work_struct`
  callbacks, kernel threads, `module_init`
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#C8E6C9"
    stroke: "#2E7D32"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-size: 12
  }
}
# ─── CANNOT SLEEP → GFP_ATOMIC ───────────────────────────────────────────────
atomic_ctx: "Spinlock Held /\nAtomic Section" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFE0B2"
    stroke: "#E65100"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 14
    bold: true
  }
}
gfp_atomic: "GFP_ATOMIC" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFCC80"
    stroke: "#BF360C"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-size: 18
    bold: true
  }
}
atomic_props: |md
  **Behavior:**
  - Never calls `schedule()` — returns immediately
  - Draws from pre-reserved emergency memory pool
  - Returns `NULL` when pool is exhausted
  - No page reclaim, no waiting
  **Success rate:** Lower under memory pressure
  **Latency:** Deterministic (nanoseconds)
  **Valid contexts:** IRQ handlers, softirqs,
  tasklets, spinlock-held regions
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFF3E0"
    stroke: "#E65100"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-size: 12
  }
}
# ─── MANDATORY NULL CHECK ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
null_check: "ALWAYS check return value" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#F3E5F5"
    stroke: "#6A1B9A"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-size: 15
    bold: true
    border-radius: 8
  }
}
null_check_code: |go
  ptr = kmalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL /* or GFP_ATOMIC */);
  if (!ptr)
      return -ENOMEM;   /* propagate up — do NOT crash */
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#EDE7F6"
    stroke: "#6A1B9A"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-size: 12
    font: mono
  }
}
# ─── PITFALL BOXES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
pitfall_kernel_in_atomic: |md
  ⚠️  **PITFALL: GFP_KERNEL in atomic context**
  Kernel detects this and calls `BUG()`:
  
  BUG: sleeping function called from
  invalid context at mm/slab.c:...
  in_atomic(): 1, irqs_disabled(): 0
  
  Machine panics immediately.
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFEBEE"
    stroke: "#B71C1C"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 12
    italic: false
  }
}
pitfall_atomic_everywhere: |md
  ⚠️  **PITFALL: GFP_ATOMIC everywhere "to be safe"**
  - Depletes the emergency memory pool
  - Increases `NULL` return frequency system-wide
  - Other drivers / kernel subsystems fail to allocate
  - Higher fragmentation, worse system stability
  - **Not conservative — it is wasteful and harmful**
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FFF3E0"
    stroke: "#E65100"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 12
  }
}
# ─── QUICK REFERENCE RULE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
golden_rule: |md
  **The One Rule:**
  *"Can the current execution context sleep?"*
  - **YES →** `GFP_KERNEL`
  - **NO  →** `GFP_ATOMIC`
  GFP flags describe **your context**, not the memory.
| {
  shape: rectangle
  near: bottom-center
  style: {
    fill: "#E3F2FD"
    stroke: "#0D47A1"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 13
    bold: true
    border-radius: 8
  }
}
# ─── CONNECTIONS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
root -> irq_ctx: "NO\n(interrupt / softirq / tasklet)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#C62828"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 13
    bold: true
    font-color: "#C62828"
  }
}
root -> proc_ctx: "YES\n(syscall, workqueue,\nkernel thread)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#2E7D32"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 13
    bold: true
    font-color: "#2E7D32"
  }
}
irq_ctx -> gfp_atomic_only {
  style: {
    stroke: "#B71C1C"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
gfp_atomic_only -> irq_note {
  style: {
    stroke: "#C62828"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 4
  }
}
proc_ctx -> can_sleep {
  style: {
    stroke: "#2E7D32"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
can_sleep -> gfp_kernel: "NO — not in atomic section\n(free to sleep)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#1B5E20"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 13
    bold: true
    font-color: "#1B5E20"
  }
}
can_sleep -> atomic_ctx: "YES — spinlock held\nor preemption disabled" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#E65100"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 13
    bold: true
    font-color: "#E65100"
  }
}
gfp_kernel -> kernel_props {
  style: {
    stroke: "#2E7D32"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 4
  }
}
atomic_ctx -> gfp_atomic {
  style: {
    stroke: "#BF360C"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}
gfp_atomic -> atomic_props {
  style: {
    stroke: "#E65100"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 4
  }
}
# Both paths converge on null check
gfp_kernel -> null_check: "always" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#6A1B9A"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 12
    font-color: "#6A1B9A"
  }
}
gfp_atomic_only -> null_check: "always\n(NULL more likely)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#6A1B9A"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 12
    font-color: "#6A1B9A"
  }
}
gfp_atomic -> null_check: "always\n(NULL more likely)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#6A1B9A"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-size: 12
    font-color: "#6A1B9A"
  }
}
null_check -> null_check_code {
  style: {
    stroke: "#6A1B9A"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
}
# Pitfall connections
pitfall_kernel_in_atomic -> gfp_atomic_only: "results in →" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#B71C1C"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 5
    font-size: 11
    font-color: "#B71C1C"
  }
}
pitfall_atomic_everywhere -> gfp_atomic: "misuse of →" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#E65100"
    stroke-width: 1
    stroke-dash: 5
    font-size: 11
    font-color: "#E65100"
  }
}